unittitle.value: Records of the Washington Square Counselor to Women Students (Berger)

extent.value: in 2 manuscript boxes and one half manuscript box

abstract.value: Dorothea Berger came to Washington Square College in 1949 as an instructor in the German Language Department. She later became Assistant to the Dean of Students and Counselor for Women Students. She was made a full professor in 1966 and became emeritus in 1973. This collection consists of her administrative records and correspondence.

p.value: Materials related to personnel, faculty grievances, job searches and all files with information that falls under the University's Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) policy are permanently restricted.

Identification of item, date (if known); Records of the Washington Square Counselor to Women Students (Berger); RG 19.4; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.
